Name: Combined
Description: Single spillway that acts as both the principal and emergency spillway.

Name: Free
Description: Surplus water falls freely from the crest of the weir; a straight drop spillway or free overfall spillway.

Name: Gated
Description: Surplus water is regulated with a gate to prevent downstream flooding.

Name: Other
Description: The spillway type of the dam structure is defined as something other than 'combined', 'free', or 'gated'.

Name: None
Description: Structure does not have a spillway.

Name: Unknown
Description: Structure has a spillway but the type is not known.
